  "notes": "Umbrian dialect (modern Romance, NOT the ancient Italic language). Central Italian of Umbria. Transitional between Tuscan and Southern varieties. Key features: (1) No gorgia. (2) Some assimilatory processes (ND→nn, MB→mm) shared with Roman. (3) Partial metaphony in eastern Umbrian varieties (Rohlfs 1966, Loporcaro 2009).",
